{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in Peru", "text_new": "{{pp-protected|small=yes}}\n{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in Peru}}\n{{Current disaster|event=disease pandemic|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Peru\n| map1            = COVID-19 Outbreak Cases in Peru.svg\n| legend1         = Departments with confirmed coronavirus cases {{legend|#FCEED3|Confirmed 1\u20139}}{{legend|#F2A88D|Confirmed 10\u201359}}{{legend|#E36654|Confirmed 60\u201399}}{{legend|#E5354B|Confirmed 100\u2013299}}<!--{{legend|#87353F|Confirmed 300-599}}--><!--{{legend|#630606|Confirmed \u2265600}}-->\n| map2            = \n| legend2         = \n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Peru]]\n| first_case      = [[Lima]]\n| arrival_date    = 6 March 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=3|day1=6|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin          = [[Czech Republic]], [[France]] and [[Spain]]\n| recovery_cases  = 4\n| deaths          = 30\n| confirmed_cases = 1,065\n| suspected_cases = \n| total_ili       = \n| website         = \n}}\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was reported to have spread to [[Peru]] on 6 March 2020 when a 25-year-old man who had traveled to Spain, France and the Czech Republic tested positive.<ref>{{cite news|accessdate=6 March 2020|title=Peru records first confirmed case of coronavirus, President Vizcarra says|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/health-coronavirus-peru-idUSE6N29R02T|newspaper=Reuters|date=6 March 2020|via=www.reuters.com}}</ref>\n__TOC__\n==Timeline==\nOn 6 March the first confirmed case in [[Peru]] was announced from a 25-year-old Peruvian living in [[Lima]] who had recently returned from travels in [[France]], [[Spain]], and [[the Czech Republic]].{{citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n\nOn 10 March 2020, 11 cases were confirmed, from which 7 of the new cases were related to the first known case in Peru.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cnnespanol.cnn.com/2020/03/10/alerta-ascienden-a-once-los-casos-de-coronavirus-en-peru/|title=Ascienden a once los casos de coronavirus en Per\u00fa|date=10 March 2020|website=CNN|language=es-ES|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref> On the following day, two new cases were registered.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://diariocorreo.pe/peru/coronavirus-en-peru-se-incrementa-a-13-el-numero-de-casos-de-coronavirus-en-peru-covid-19-noticia/|title=Coronavirus en Per\u00fa: Se incrementa a 13 el n\u00famero de casos|last=Correo|first=Redacci\u00f3n|date=11 March 2020|website=Correo|language=es|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref> Due to the global pandemic, the Peruvian government decided to cancel classes in public and private schools, as a precautionary measure until 30 March.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://diariocorreo.pe/politica/martin-vizcarra-clases-en-colegios-publicos-se-postergaron-hasta-el-30-de-marzo-por-coronavirus-peru-medidas-preventivas-noticia/|title=No hay clases en colegios p\u00fablicos y privados hasta el 30 de marzo, anuncia Vizcarra|last=Correo|first=Redacci\u00f3n|date=11 March 2020|website=Correo|language=es|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 March, Peruvian President Mart\u00edn Vizcarra made a national announcement, declaring a 15-day quarantine effective from 16 March, effectively putting in place stringent rules 9 days after the first case was seen in the country. There was a sudden ban on all travel between provinces, all travel into and out of the country, and a ban put on place for planes, boats, trains, buses, and private automobiles.<ref>[https://gestion.pe/peru/politica/coronavirus-en-peru-gobierno-anuncia-cuarentena-obligatorio-por-15-dias-por-coronavirus-noticia/] {{in lang|es}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 March, group of four Mexicans from [[Tamaulipas]] who went to [[Cusco]], on vacation could not return to Mexico until 2 April because all flights had been canceled and the borders of Peru were closed.<ref>[https://www.informador.mx/mexico/Cierre-de-fronteras-deja-varados-a-mexicanos-en-Peru-20200316-0133.html Border closure leaves Mexicans stranded in Peru] {{in lang|es}} Informador, 16 March 2020</ref> Furthermore, thousands of American, Israeli, Australian, and British tourists trapped mostly in Cusco and Lima were unable to leave the country in the 24 hours between announcement of the quarantine and cessation of all flights. On this day, the President also announced a sum of 380 soles ($106 at the time) would be given to vulnerable families to help while most people are unable to work.<ref>[https://larepublica.pe/economia/2020/03/16/martin-vizcarra-anuncia-bono-de-380-soles-a-personas-que-cumplan-trabajos-diarios/]{{in lang|es}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 March, the second full day of quarantine, citizens were required to fill out an online form in order to obtain permission to leave home.<ref>[https://canaln.pe/actualidad/coronavirus-mininter-habilita-web-solicitar-pase-especial-transito-n408558]{{in lang|es}}</ref> Military paraded the streets of Lima to enforce this, and people were not allowed to walk together. At 8pm that night through an organized effort, Peruvians and residents in Peru went out to their balconies and windows to applaud the front-line workers such as doctors, the military, market shop owners, and police to applaud their efforts during the pandemic.<ref>[https://larepublica.pe/sociedad/2020/03/18/coronavirus-en-peru-ciudadanos-agradecen-con-aplausos-a-medicos-que-combaten-el-covid-19-video-fotos/]{{in lang|es}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 March, the government tightened the measures of quarantine, implementing a curfew from 8pm-5am where citizens are not allowed to leave their homes. A man who was seen taking out the trash that night was cornered by a dozen police cars and motorcycles, and arrested.<ref>[https://larepublica.pe/sociedad/2020/03/19/facebook-toque-de-queda-hombre-que-saco-la-basura-durante-medida-fue-detenido-video-mdga/] {{in lang|es}}</ref> 153 other people in Lima and Callao were detained that night for violating curfew.<ref>[https://larepublica.pe/sociedad/2020/03/19/toque-de-queda-mas-de-100-detenidos-en-lima-y-callao-por-no-acatar-medida-video-mdga/] {{in lang|es}}</ref>\n\nOn 19 March, MINSA informed about the first death because of the virus, a 78-year-old man.<ref>[https://libero.pe/ocio/1546768-coronavirus-peru-ministerio-salud-confirma-primer-paciente-peruano-fallecido-covid-19-minsa-lima?ref=alerta] {{in lang|es}}</ref> On the same day, the death toll was updated to 3.<ref>[https://elcomercio.pe/lima/sucesos/coronavirus-en-peru-en-vivo-en-directo-cuarto-dia-de-emergencia-toque-de-queda-y-145-casos-confirmados-covid-19-estado-de-emergencia-martin-vizcarra-noticia/] {{in lang|es}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Alrededores del ex terminal Fiori en San Mart\u00edn de Porres durante el Estado de Emergencia Covid-19.jpg|thumb|People in Lima wearing facemasks on 16 March]]\nOn 20 March, President Vizcarra announced that Elizabeth Hinostroza would be stepping down from her post as Minister of Health in favor of Victor Zamora Mesia, who the President stated had more experience in the public health sector and was more experienced in the face of this pandemic.<ref>[https://peru21.pe/peru/coronavirus-en-peru-reemplazan-a-elizabeth-hinostroza-como-ministra-de-salud-estado-de-emergencia-noticia/] {{in lang|es}}</ref> The President was also quoted as saying that if all citizens respect the quarantine and abide properly by its laws, the state of emergency could be lifted at the end of the 15-day quarantine,<ref>[https://rpp.pe/politica/gobierno/coronavirus-en-peru-martin-vizcarra-si-los-dias-que-quedan-los-trabajamos-bien-no-seria-necesario-ampliar-estado-de-emergencia-noticia-1253069] {{in lang|es}}</ref> a relief in the face of bordering countries such as Chile declaring a 90-day state of emergency.\n\nOn 26 March, President Vizcarra made a national announcement that the quarantine will be amplified by 13 days, lasting until Sunday, April 12, inclusive. He cited the number of infringements of quarantine, especially in the north of the country in the La Libertad department.\n\nOn 30 March, the President made further restrictions to the curfew (which was previously 8pm to 5am nationwide), extending its start from 4pm for departments of La Libertad, Loreto, Piura, and Tumbes, and a start of 6 pm for the rest of the country to further limit movement. As a response, grocery stores which were open until 4 pm before now close at 3 pm. As of this date, there were 950 positive tests, 24 deaths, 49 patients in the ICU, and 37 on mechanical ventilation. <ref>[http://www.elperuano.pe/noticia-sube-a-950-numero-contagiados-y-24-fallecidos-covid19-el-peru-93681.aspx]{{in lang|es}} </ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Date\n! Total Cases\n! Lima Cases\n|-\n| 2020-03-06\n| 1 <ref>{{cite news|accessdate=14 March 2020|title=Peru records first confirmed case of coronavirus, President Vizcarra says|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/health-coronavirus-peru-idUSE6N29R02T|newspaper=Reuters|date=6 March 2020|via=www.reuters.com}}</ref>\n| 1\n|-\n| 2020-03-07\n| 6 <ref>{{cite news|accessdate=14 March 2020|title=Peru reports 5 new cases of coronavirus, one day after announcing its first|url=https://www.infobae.com/america/agencias/2020/03/07/peru-reporta-cinco-nuevos-casos-de-coronavirus-un-dia-despues-de-anunciar-el-primero/|newspaper=Infobae (Spanish)|date=6 March 2020|via=www.infobae.com}}</ref>\n| 5\n|-\n| 2020-03-08\n| 7\n| 6\n|-\n| 2020-03-09\n| 9\n| 8\n|-\n| 2020-03-10\n| 11 <ref>[https://www.indeci.gob.pe/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/REPORTE-COMPLEMENTARIO-N%C2%BA-1250-10MAR2020-CASOS-CONFIRMADOS-DE-CORONAVIRUS-EN-EL-PER%C3%9A-2.pdf INDECI report]</ref>\n| 8\n|-\n| 2020-03-11\n| 15 <ref>[https://rpp.pe/peru/actualidad/minsa-eleva-a-15-los-casos-confirmados-por-el-nuevo-coronavirus-noticia-1250939 Minsa: Sube a 17 los casos confirmados del nuevo coronavirus en el Per\u00fa ]</ref>\n| 11\n|-\n| 2020-03-12\n| 22 <ref>[https://www.expreso.com.pe/actualidad/coronavirus-en-peru-se-eleva-a-22-la-cifra-de-casos-actualizacion/ Coronavirus en Per\u00fa: sube a 38 la cifra de contagiados ]</ref>\n| 17\n|-\n| 2020-03-13\n| 38 <ref>[https://www.expreso.com.pe/actualidad/coronavirus-en-peru-se-eleva-a-22-la-cifra-de-casos-actualizacion/ Coronavirus en Per\u00fa: sube a 38 la cifra de contagiados ]</ref>\n| 32\n|-\n| 2020-03-14\n\n| 43\n| 37\n|-\n|2020-03-15\n| 71\n| 58\n|-\n|2020-03-16\n| 86\n| 70\n|-\n|2020-03-17\n|117\n|96\n|-\n|2020-03-18\n|145\n|111\n|-\n|2020-03-19\n|234\n|194\n|-\n|2020-03-20\n|263\n|212\n|-\n|2020-03-21\n|318\n|241\n|-\n|2020-03-22\n|361 <ref>[https://gestion.pe/peru/numero-de-infectado-de-covid-19-se-eleva-a-363-en-peru-lima-registra-278-casos-emergencia-por-coronavirus-periodo-de-inmovilizacion-obligatoria-estado-de-emergencia-toque-de-queda-disponen-covid-19-nndc-noticia/] {{in lang|es}}</ref>\n|278\n|-\n|2020-03-23\n|395\n|307\n|-\n|2020-03-24\n|416 <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://giscorporativo.com.pe/covid19_regiones.html|website=giscorporativo.com.pe|access-date=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n|322\n|-\n|2020-03-25\n|480\n|369\n|-\n|2020-03-26\n|580\n|453\n|-\n|2020-03-27\n|635\n|494\n|-\n|2020-03-28\n|671\n|518\n|-\n|2020-03-29\n|852 <ref>[https://diariocorreo.pe/peru/coronavirus-peru-cifra-de-contagiados-por-covid-19-aumenta-181-en-un-dia-noticia/]{{in lang|es}}</ref>\n|639\n|-\n|2020-03-30\n|950 <ref>[http://www.elperuano.pe/noticia-sube-a-950-numero-contagiados-y-24-fallecidos-covid19-el-peru-93681.aspx] {{in lang|es}} </ref>\n|718\n|-\n|2020-03-31\n|1,065\n|\n|}\n\n==Statistics==\n\n{{Medical cases chart\n    |barwidth=wide\n    |numwidth=tw\n    |float=none\n    |disease=COVID-19\n    |location=Peru\n    |outbreak=2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic\n    |recoveries=y\n    |rows=\n      {{Medical cases chart/Row|2020-03-06|||1|||1||divisor=3|numwidth=tw}}\n      {{Medical cases chart/Row|2020-03